Description: Solid, ovoid shaped stamp with a flat base, made of white limestone. The upper side contains a small perforation, drilled through from both sides with an outer diameter of 0.9 to an inner diameter of 0.3 cm. Some faint cracking is evident on the objects outer surface. The base shows a small oval depression on one end and several very crudely incised lines. Probably functioned as a crude stamp.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.15D, between levels 1-2
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 151)
